    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This cluster of sensitive wire whiskers fits over the nose or snout to provide sensory information as it reacts to nearby odors and other scents. A creature wearing *olfactory stimulators* gains a sense of smell, which is as precise as an average member of its species, as well as the scent special ability if members of its species typically have that ability. *Olfactory stimulators* can be fitted to animal companions as well as sapient creatures; stimulators produced for companion use have the companion trait.",
